<i>I have never seen your mum
so upset.</i>

20:14.422 --> 20:16.414
<i>Christ.
- Sorry?</i>

20:16.465 --> 20:18.047
Yeah, er...

20:18.092 --> 20:20.800
<i>So, um, what do you
want me to say?</i>

20:20.845 --> 20:22.928
<i>'Cause she asked me to phone,
you know.</i>

20:22.972 --> 20:24.258
Well...

20:26.934 --> 20:27.890
It's...

20:27.935 --> 20:30.803
<i>It's not true, obviously, I'm not
with a gori or anybody.</i>

20:30.855 --> 20:32.972
I'm not with anyone, Auntie.

20:35.276 --> 20:37.734
Auntie, I'll call you back.
I've got a meeting.

20:37.778 --> 20:39.314
Give me 10 minutes.
I'll get right back to you.

20:39.363 --> 20:40.399
Thank you.

20:40.448 --> 20:42.565
Laura...
- Just popping round the shop.

20:52.126 --> 20:53.082
Laura.

20:53.127 --> 20:54.868
You just told someone
I don't exist.

20:54.920 --> 20:56.502
No...
- What do you mean, no?

20:56.547 --> 20:58.334
It was my auntie.
I was ambushed.

20:58.382 --> 21:00.214
I had to say that.

21:00.259 --> 21:02.467
Otherwise it'd spread like wildfire

21:02.511 --> 21:05.800
and it can't... it can't happen
that way.

21:05.848 --> 21:07.931
It just can't.

21:07.975 --> 21:10.183
Those were just words.
- Not to me.

21:10.227 --> 21:14.062
I've said, I've told you
I'm gonna tell my mum and I am.

21:16.776 --> 21:18.483
When did your parents get back?

21:19.987 --> 21:23.856
The day before yesterday.
- And you didn't tell me?

21:25.075 --> 21:27.533
It's delicate. That's all.

21:27.578 --> 21:30.286
It's about doing it right. Yeah?

21:30.331 --> 21:34.120
I have 54 first cousins
and so far all of them have...

21:34.168 --> 21:36.410
Married a Sikh girl or a Sikh boy.
I know this.

21:36.420 --> 21:39.003
Yeah, and I'm the one
who's going to break ranks.

21:39.799 --> 21:41.540
I'll be the first, Laura.

21:41.592 --> 21:45.051
I mean, it's possible and probable
I'll be disowned.

21:45.095 --> 21:48.133
What, so, you'll never tell them
about me because...

21:48.933 --> 21:50.219
you can't.

21:51.060 --> 21:53.268
You'll just live two separate lives.

21:54.063 --> 21:55.725
You're wrong.

21:55.773 --> 21:57.264
You are so wrong.

21:58.818 --> 22:01.435
I'm gonna drive up and tell them now.

22:02.655 --> 22:04.612
And I mean right now!

22:04.657 --> 22:06.398
Enough is enough.

22:35.563 --> 22:37.099
SATHNAM SIGHS

22:54.957 --> 22:58.576
FRONT DOOR OPENS AND SHUTS

23:00.462 --> 23:01.623
Sathnam?

23:06.260 --> 23:07.421
Mum...

23:10.139 --> 23:11.880
Jugi wants to thank you.

23:15.311 --> 23:18.679
And now you've come to see me.
SHE SPEAKS PUNJABI

23:20.107 --> 23:21.143
There's...

23:32.953 --> 23:36.788
She looks like Cheryl Cole.
So pretty.

23:36.832 --> 23:38.664
MOBILE PHONE BUZZES
- So...

23:40.544 --> 23:43.036
Huh? Shall I arrange for it?

23:43.088 --> 23:44.545
<i>Yes, huna?</i>

23:44.590 --> 23:46.627
Yes, yes, you leave it to me,
I'll fix it.

23:50.262 --> 23:52.470
DISHWARE CLATTERS

23:53.974 --> 23:56.136
SHOPPING CHANNEL
PLAYS ON TV

24:17.373 --> 24:18.830
What are you reading about,
Dedi?

24:19.667 --> 24:21.499
What's in the paper?
What's it say?

24:22.836 --> 24:24.543
I'm reading about America.

24:26.840 --> 24:30.709
I am reading about the
Prime Minister of America.

24:31.762 --> 24:32.798
Isn't it?

24:33.931 --> 24:35.513
There are two governments.

24:36.433 --> 24:37.719
One there and one here

24:37.768 --> 24:40.852
and they both work very closely.

24:41.939 --> 24:42.975
Don't they?

24:43.023 --> 24:45.857
You mean the American and
British governments?

24:45.859 --> 24:47.100
Mm-hmm.
- Yeah.

24:53.951 --> 24:56.193
Do you understand the words
and letters in English, Dedi?

24:56.245 --> 24:57.736
Can you actually read any of it?

25:02.835 --> 25:06.954
Oh, that's great. I wish Mum would
learn to read English.

25:07.006 --> 25:09.168
It's important.

25:16.056 --> 25:18.890
We have a Sathnam alert.

25:20.310 --> 25:21.551
Sathnam.

25:23.897 --> 25:25.104
Sathnam.

25:26.316 --> 25:28.103
Sathnam Sanghera.

25:28.944 --> 25:30.401
Sathnam.

25:32.031 --> 25:33.021
Sathnam.

25:36.493 --> 25:38.359
Can I tell you something?

25:39.621 --> 25:41.408
Yeah, yeah, sure.

25:42.541 --> 25:45.204
Your mum tells me not to talk
about this with you.

25:46.378 --> 25:48.540
It's fine, I won't say anything.

25:51.091 --> 25:52.923
When the sun rises...

25:57.097 --> 26:01.888
But everything is OK because
I can raise the sun.

26:04.438 --> 26:07.681
Yeah.
- I can raise the sun.

26:09.276 --> 26:12.269
And I have worked it out myself.

26:19.912 --> 26:21.574
MOBILE PHONE BUZZES

26:23.540 --> 26:25.122
BUZZING STOPS

26:39.056 --> 26:41.764
His outpatient appointment
for tomorrow.

26:44.019 --> 26:46.727
Nothing special.
Regular check-up.

26:49.817 --> 26:51.353
No need to come.

27:09.378 --> 27:12.166
RANDOM MUTTERINGS
IN WAITING ROOM

27:21.056 --> 27:22.888
MAN MUMBLES

27:34.653 --> 27:36.861
Would you like to follow me
to Dr Dutta's office?

27:36.905 --> 27:37.816
Yeah.

27:40.367 --> 27:42.108
It's the last door on the left.

27:45.706 --> 27:47.572
KNOCK ON DOOR
- DOCTOR: Come in.

27:50.419 --> 27:51.500
Hi.

27:51.545 --> 27:53.582
FATHER GREETS IN PUNJABI

27:55.424 --> 27:57.837
GREETINGS IN PUNJABI

27:58.969 --> 28:01.052
Mum, Mum, just sit down.

28:04.266 --> 28:05.802
DOCTOR:
I have not seen you before.

28:06.310 --> 28:08.222
Your sisters and brother, yes,
but not you.

28:08.270 --> 28:09.431
I live in London.

28:09.479 --> 28:13.439
I just wanted to know a bit more
about my father's, erm, condition.

28:13.483 --> 28:15.475
Yes, no problem, no problem.

28:24.995 --> 28:29.490
OK, one for the heart, blood pressure,
diabetes.

28:29.541 --> 28:32.158
Ah, and these are for
his mental health problems.

28:32.211 --> 28:34.669
Your father is on Quetiapine.

28:34.713 --> 28:37.922
And a monthly injection
of Modecate.

28:37.966 --> 28:40.128
Injections?
- DOCTOR CHUCKLES

28:40.177 --> 28:42.794
Your father is not so reliable
when it comes to taking his medicines

28:42.846 --> 28:47.011
so it's just a backup to ensure he doesn't
deteriorate beyond a certain point.

28:47.059 --> 28:48.175
Jagjit...

29:07.579 --> 29:10.242
And, erm, I can make the sun rise

29:10.290 --> 29:12.327
and both the countries are friends,
I know that.

29:12.376 --> 29:13.742
Thank you very much.

29:16.463 --> 29:17.920
DOCTOR:
Are you alright?

29:19.967 --> 29:21.799
Yeah.

29:21.843 --> 29:24.586
I've just never seen him
so animated.

29:24.638 --> 29:27.221
At home, he just, you know,
reads the newspaper

29:27.266 --> 29:31.510
or watches the Shopping Channel,
I mean, obsessively.

29:31.561 --> 29:34.304
He may think it's talking to him
or about him.

29:34.815 --> 29:37.102
But if he's becoming delusional,
let's nip it in the bud.

29:37.150 --> 29:39.688
We'll increase his dose.
- Don't... don't do it on my say-so.

29:39.736 --> 29:41.853
Ah, please, I've been monitoring
him for some time.

29:41.905 --> 29:43.897
I think it'll be good to
increase a little.

29:43.949 --> 29:46.191
With his agreement, of course.

29:46.243 --> 29:47.654
Jagjit...

29:50.539 --> 29:51.825
<i>You're taking two, huna?</i>

29:54.835 --> 29:57.248
So to keep you well,
we will keep it the same

29:57.296 --> 29:58.912
but we'll just double the dosage.

30:06.013 --> 30:07.470
Thank you very much.
Thank you.

30:08.598 --> 30:12.012
You should know that your father
is only doing as well as he is

30:12.060 --> 30:13.096
because of your mother.

30:13.145 --> 30:16.138
She enables him to remain at home.

30:16.189 --> 30:18.226
Although, and I say this
with some pride

30:18.275 --> 30:21.689
Indian families cope because
the entire family rallies around.

30:21.737 --> 30:26.107
I promise you, 95 out of 100
people like your father

30:26.158 --> 30:29.617
would be in a nursing home by now,
and a closed unit, at that.

30:30.871 --> 30:32.453
Try not to worry.

30:32.497 --> 30:34.204
Continuity is everything.

30:34.249 --> 30:36.241
It's change that causes the problems.

30:36.293 --> 30:38.330
Change can throw him off balance.

30:38.378 --> 30:42.167
But, well, since we have seen
no aggression for many years and...

30:42.215 --> 30:45.458
What, aggression?
What do you mean, aggression?

30:45.510 --> 30:49.003
No, I mean, he's...
- Please, remember what I said.

30:49.848 --> 30:53.216
Let us not be at loggerheads.
- Oh, he's used to people arguing.

30:53.268 --> 30:54.975
But not you with me.

30:56.063 --> 30:57.395
So...

31:01.902 --> 31:03.814
DOCTOR: Jagjit...
- Not to worry.

31:04.404 --> 31:05.895
THEY SPEAK PUNJABI
- Thank you.

31:17.751 --> 31:20.209
SATHNAM: Yeah, he was admitted
to hospital last night.

31:20.253 --> 31:21.460
<i>LAURA:
That's terrible.</i>

31:21.505 --> 31:24.543
Yeah, so I just felt I couldn't
bring us up now.

31:24.591 --> 31:26.674
You know, 'cause the doctor
said at times like this

31:26.718 --> 31:29.256
the only reason my dad's not being
transferred to a secure unit

31:29.304 --> 31:32.797
is because his family life is stable.

31:34.226 --> 31:35.216
<i>Right.</i>

31:35.268 --> 31:37.851
I mean, you do see that,
don't you?

31:37.896 --> 31:39.933
<i>Of course I do. Yeah, of course.</i>

31:41.358 --> 31:42.314
OK.

31:42.359 --> 31:44.942
Listen, do you want me to call Greg
and get the interview rearranged?

31:44.986 --> 31:46.648
What time does your dad get
out of hospital?

31:46.696 --> 31:47.812
What do you mean, out of hosp...?

31:48.448 --> 31:50.235
Yeah, yeah, you should.

31:53.120 --> 31:54.702
Oh, my God.

31:55.455 --> 31:56.866
<i>You've lied to me.
- Yeah, no...</i>

31:56.915 --> 31:58.702
<i>Look, Laura, listen.</i>

32:03.755 --> 32:05.337
Sathnam...

32:08.593 --> 32:10.380
The editor's coming back to London.

32:10.429 --> 32:11.886
Sorry.

32:11.930 --> 32:14.343
Is it really urgent?
- Very.

32:14.391 --> 32:16.348
Important?
- SATHNAM SIGHS

32:20.230 --> 32:21.687
MOBILE PHONE RINGS

32:24.109 --> 32:26.772
Sathnam, fuck off.

32:30.532 --> 32:31.739
CAR ENGINE REVS

32:39.166 --> 32:40.873
She's on her way to Lisbon.

32:41.501 --> 32:42.742
For the travel pages.

32:42.794 --> 32:44.581
Who else is on that piece?
Is Matt on that?

32:44.629 --> 32:46.336
GREG:
Sathnam, quick word.

32:48.758 --> 32:51.751
Now, Laura has asked us to
withhold her contact details from you.

32:52.512 --> 32:54.424
Now I've no idea what's going on
between you two

32:54.473 --> 32:55.930
but we're all professionals,
alright?

32:55.974 --> 32:58.136
Matt's out in Lisbon, too, isn't he?

32:58.185 --> 32:59.221
Matt's over there.

33:01.313 --> 33:02.804
Sathnam...

33:03.231 --> 33:05.473
Sathnam, listen, mate.
There's lots to concentrate on, yeah?

33:05.525 --> 33:06.561
You've got your interview
with Simon Cowell...

33:06.610 --> 33:08.397
SATHNAM SCOFFS
- Sathnam!

33:10.071 --> 33:12.529
Laura, come on.
- LAURA: Your stuff's down there.

33:12.574 --> 33:13.860
Changing the locks?

33:13.909 --> 33:15.616
Take your stuff and go.

33:15.660 --> 33:16.696
What about our new flat?

33:16.745 --> 33:18.611
You love that place.
We've just put a deposit down.

33:18.663 --> 33:20.495
Yeah, you've lost that, too.

33:20.790 --> 33:22.122
Take your bags and go.

33:22.834 --> 33:23.950
I don't want to.

33:28.340 --> 33:29.205
Laura!

33:33.303 --> 33:34.510
What?

33:34.554 --> 33:37.297
What exactly do you want
to say to me, Sathnam?

33:39.309 --> 33:41.346
Right, yeah. Absolutely nothing.

33:41.394 --> 33:43.101
Oh, this is... I can't...

33:43.146 --> 33:44.978
My dad's illiterate but I went
to Cambridge!

33:45.023 --> 33:47.606
I got a First! Big deal!

33:47.651 --> 33:50.689
If it makes you so much better than them,
what are you hiding from?

33:50.737 --> 33:52.478
'Cause that's what you're doing!

33:52.531 --> 33:54.693
Let's pretend my dad was never ill

33:54.741 --> 33:57.028
and let's keep the peasants up in
Wolverhampton

33:57.077 --> 33:59.034
while I have another life down here!

33:59.079 --> 34:02.663
Which, incredibly, given you don't know
the basic facts about your own family

34:02.707 --> 34:06.747
includes a job where you're paid to ask
strangers about their lives.

34:06.795 --> 34:08.036
Brilliant.

34:08.088 --> 34:10.956
<i>Also, just imagine your reaction
if it was me telling you</i>

34:11.007 --> 34:13.670
I can't introduce you to my family
because you're Punjabi!

34:13.717 --> 34:15.208
That's not the same.
That is not the same!

34:15.219 --> 34:17.382
It's a bit the same, Sathnam!
- Not at all, actually

34:17.429 --> 34:18.966
because Sikhs believe
all human beings

34:19.014 --> 34:21.678
even though they appear different,
are one, we are all one, Laura!

34:21.726 --> 34:24.264
Then what's the fucking problem?

34:27.732 --> 34:29.143
HE YELLS

34:46.042 --> 34:47.748
CAR DOOR SLAMS
- SATHNAM: Laura!

